The paper discusses the mathematical workings of recommendation algorithms, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also mentions the development of a MOOC, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cyberlearning (cs.CY). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI) as recommender systems often rely on network analysis.
